.TH "fc_vport_setup" 9 "fc_vport_setup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fc_vport_setup \- allocates and creates a FC virtual port.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fc_vport_setup
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ","
.BI "int channel "  ","
.BI "struct device *pdev "  ","
.BI "struct fc_vport_identifiers *ids "  ","
.BI "struct fc_vport **ret_vport "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
scsi host the virtual port is connected to.
.IP "channel" 12
Channel on shost port connected to.
.IP "pdev" 12
parent device for vport
.IP "ids" 12
The world wide names, FC4 port roles, etc for
the virtual port.
.IP "ret_vport" 12
The pointer to the created vport.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates and creates the vport structure, calls the parent host
to instantiate the vport, this completes w/ class and sysfs creation.
.SH "NOTES"
This routine assumes no locks are held on entry.
